snippet.textDisplay: Yall are thick skulled and dont get it. Firstly, every truck is ugly. There has never been a sleek or hot looking truck on the road that made me go, wow thats a nice looking truck. The purpose of a truck is utility and function, not looks. The point of this shape is it makes creating this unibody exoskeleton in stainless steel a single stamp process, avoiding all paint (which scratches anyway if you're truly using a truck for what it's meant for) and other slow and expensive processes. This is how Tesla is able to give you this truck at 39k with autopilot and such crazy specs. It won't scratch or dent, the windows may shatter but not as easily, and it can tow and hold a lot of payload. That's what trucks are for. Not to mention the cost of ownership on this thing will halve its price.
